The paper deals with game theory and optimization in the context of load balancing, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. "cs.GT" (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) is the most likely category, as the paper explicitly mentions Nash equilibria and strong Nash equilibria. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) and "cs.IT" (Information Theory) are also possible categories, as the paper involves analyzing the performance of algorithms and making use of graph-theoretic tools. "cs.NE" (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category, as load balancing is a common problem in network design. Finally, "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible given the focus on analyzing the stability of equilibria in a game-theoretic setting.
